Package org.anchoranalysis.bean

Defining, loading, initializing Anchor Beans.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GenerateUniqueParameterization
    Objects that must implement well-defined equals() and hashCode() methods and also generate a name uniquely identifying the class and all parameterization
    StringBeanCollection
    A bean that provides a collection of Strings.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnchorBean<F>
    The base class of all beans used in Anchor.
    BeanInstanceMap
    Maps a AnchorBean family-type to some beans belong to the family.
    FieldAccessor
    Utilities to access a Field of an AnchorBean.
    NamedBean<T extends AnchorBean<?>>
    A bean with an associated textual name.
    NullParamsBean<T>
    A base class for beans that require initialization but the initializations needs no parameters.
    OptionalFactory
    Utility functions to create Optional from nullable providers or boolean flags.
    StringList
    A list of strings (order is defined).
    StringSet
    A set of strings.

Package org.anchoranalysis.bean Description

Defining, loading, initializing Anchor Beans.

In contrast to convention, unlike other packages whose namespace includes .bean., not all public-classes in this package are anchor-beans.
